00:07:06,060 --> 00:07:08,860
then the photon will again go through.

154
00:07:10,440 --> 00:07:13,020
So we can think of the

155
00:07:13,020 --> 00:07:15,600
polarizer as both a preparer of systems,

156
00:07:15,600 --> 00:07:19,160
it prepares a photon with a particular polarization,

157
00:07:19,580 --> 00:07:22,840
and it can also be thought of as a detector,

158
00:07:23,100 --> 00:07:24,720
or better yet,

159
00:07:24,720 --> 00:07:28,840
a measuring apparatus that measures the photon polarization.

160
00:07:29,400 --> 00:07:30,360
In particular,

161
00:07:30,360 --> 00:07:33,640
if the photon was horizontally polarized,

162
00:07:33,980 --> 00:07:36,180
it will pass through the horizontal polarizer.

163
00:07:36,320 --> 00:07:37,540
On the other hand,

164
00:07:37,540 --> 00:07:40,820
if the photon was created vertically polarized,

165
00:07:41,060 --> 00:07:42,600
I don't need to put arrows on these things,

166
00:07:42,740 --> 00:07:44,120
it's good enough just to put a direction.

167
00:07:44,120 --> 00:07:47,960
If the photon is created vertically polarized,

168
00:07:50,960 --> 00:07:55,120
and the apparatus is horizontally polarized,

169
00:07:55,580 --> 00:07:57,940
then the photon will not go through the apparatus.

170
00:07:58,200 --> 00:07:59,320
It may get reflected,

171
00:07:59,320 --> 00:08:01,400
or it may just get absorbed,

172
00:08:01,400 --> 00:08:02,760
one or the other.

173
00:08:03,820 --> 00:08:05,520
But whichever it does,

174
00:08:05,520 --> 00:08:07,590
by monitoring whether the photon

175
00:08:07,590 --> 00:08:09,660
goes through over here or not,

176
00:08:09,900 --> 00:08:11,750
you have measured whether the

177
00:08:11,750 --> 00:08:13,600
