183
00:08:31,140 --> 00:08:33,659
and would admit a vertical flag,

184
00:08:33,659 --> 00:08:35,159
and vice versa.

185
00:08:35,480 --> 00:08:37,220
There's nothing particularly,

186
00:08:37,220 --> 00:08:39,539
and this is entirely deterministic,

187
00:08:39,740 --> 00:08:41,520
if you send the photon,

188
00:08:41,520 --> 00:08:43,520
if the photon is vertically polarized,

189
00:08:44,000 --> 00:08:45,040
it'll pass through.

190
00:08:45,160 --> 00:08:46,520
If it's horizontally polarized,

191
00:08:46,520 --> 00:08:47,720
it won't pass through.

192
00:08:47,900 --> 00:08:48,780
End of story.

193
00:08:49,160 --> 00:08:52,300
Nothing out of the ordinary there.

194
00:08:54,220 --> 00:08:56,840
The place where the out of the ordinary happens

195
00:08:57,520 --> 00:08:58,890
is when we add to

