You can check that out

2538
01:46:31,400 --> 01:46:33,040
and see if it makes any sense to you

2539
01:46:33,040 --> 01:46:35,940
by trying it out for some angles

2540
01:46:35,940 --> 01:46:37,060
and seeing if it makes sense.

2541
01:46:37,560 --> 01:46:39,180
But we could do the same thing

2542
01:46:39,180 --> 01:46:41,040
with any observable.

2543
01:46:42,740 --> 01:46:44,520
Any observable and any vector,

2544
01:46:44,660 --> 01:46:45,840
we could calculate the...

2545
01:46:46,460 --> 01:46:47,440
Not the probability,

2546
01:46:47,740 --> 01:46:51,700
but the average of the observable.

2547
01:46:52,240 --> 01:46:53,860
I will use the standard

2548
01:46:53,880 --> 01:46:56,060
terminology and call it

2549
01:46:56,060 --> 01:46:57,140
the expectation value,

2550
01:46:57,460 --> 01:46:58,900
but keep in mind that

2551
01:46:58,900 --> 01:47:00,240
that really is a misnomer.

2552
01:47:00,360 --> 01:47:01,960
It should be just the average value.

2553
01:47:03,760 --> 01:47:04,340
Good.

2554
